text: The Lusatian – New Marchian dialects (German: Lausitzisch-Neumärkisch) are High German dialects spoken in Berlin, central and southern Brandenburg, central and southern Saxony-Anhalt, and in northwestern and eastern Saxony. == References == Category:German dialects Category:Languages of Germany Category:Berlin Category:Brandenburg Category:Saxony Category:Saxony-Anhalt
title: South Markish dialects
